      "type": "thinking",
      "text": "**Considering New Feature Integration**\n\nI'm currently focused on integrating a \"Text to Image\" feature into the TriAttach Image Generator. My initial thought is that this will be another mode alongside \"Generate Image\" and \"Describe Image\". I need to figure out the best way to structure it and how to minimize the changes to the existing structure. I'm thinking I'll need a new backend API endpoint.\n\n\n**Refining Feature Implementation**\n\nI've refined the feature integration plan, structuring it as three distinct modes. \"Generate Image\" (Image-to-Image/Prompting) remains, \"Image to Prompt\" (Describe) is retained, and \"Text to Image\" is the new mode. My plan includes updating the `AppMode` type, the UI to include tabs, and implementing the new mode's logic. I'll need to create a dedicated function in `geminiService.ts` for text-to-image or update the existing one.\n\n\n**Revising Mode Functionality**\n\nI'm revisiting the feature's structure. Thinking the \"Generate Image\" part can function with zero images, yet, the user desired three sections. This is leading me to define three distinct modes: \"text2image,\" requiring only a prompt, \"mixmatch,\" using both prompt and images, and \"describe,\" converting images to prompts. I'm planning UI updates with three mode-selection buttons and conditional input fields, along with modifying `geminiService.ts`.\n\n\n",
      "cMarkNode": {}
    },
