    "id": 9,
    "author": "model",
    "payload": {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "### Specification for \"TriAttach Image Generator\" Update\n\nI will update the application to support three distinct AI creation modes as requested, following a professional 3-section layout.\n\n#### 1. Three Modes of Operation\n*   **Text to Image**: Pure text-based generation. The image upload section is hidden to keep the focus on the prompt.\n*   **Mix & Match**: Multimodal generation. Combines your text prompt with 1–3 reference images to guide the AI's visual output.\n*   **Img to Prompt**: Analytical mode. Analyzes 1–3 images to extract a detailed descriptive prompt that can be used for future generations.\n\n#### 2. Visual & Functional Behavior\n*   **Dynamic UI**: The input panel adapts based on the selected tab. Non-relevant inputs (like the prompt box in \"Img to Prompt\" mode) are hidden or transformed.\n*   **Input Handling**: \n    *   **Text to Image**: Requires only a prompt.\n    *   **Mix & Match**: Requires at least one image and a prompt.\n    *   **Img to Prompt**: Requires at least one image.\n*   **Result Persistence**: The output panel clearly distinguishes between \"Image Results\" and \"Prompt Results\" with specific actions (Download for images, Copy for text).\n*   **Aesthetics**: A deep charcoal background (`bg-gray-900`) with glassmorphism effects on panels. Gradient buttons and animated loading states ensure a \"world-class\" feel.\n\n---\n\n",
      "cMarkNode": {}
    },
